This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with human activity recognition from videos. It also involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in computer vision research. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and long short-term memory (LSTM) networks, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). 

Furthermore, the paper involves the analysis and processing of multimedia data, which falls under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM). 

Finally, the paper involves the use of attention mechanisms to learn latent sub-events, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves the extraction of relevant information from videos.
